returns the smallest prime that divides n

  - returns 1 if n=1, n=-1, or n is not an integer

name: src/index.js
src/stats/BaseStats.js
BaseStats
description: A stat collector that initially includes no collector functions.

name: addCollector
description:
Add a collector function that can process data
when process() or get() is called.

params.name: collector
params.description:
An object with the following properties:
  - **name** - [String] The name of the collector
  - **initialValue** - [any] The initial value if update() has never been called
  - **requirements** - [Array] An array of collector names that must be added before this collector
  - **handleProcess** - [Function]
  - **handleGet** - [Function]

name: src/stats/number/AdvancedNumberStats.js
AdvancedNumberStats
description:
A stat collector that includes the following collector functions:
  - count
  - sum
  - min
  - max
  - mean
  - powerSumAvg_running
  - variance_running
  - standardDeviation_running
  - sumOfSquaredDeviations_stable
  - variance_stable
  - standardDeviation_stable
  - count_* (a bunch of filtered counts)
